1
00:00:01,133 --> 00:00:02,700
<i>It was supposed to be
your reconciliation dinner.</i>

2
00:00:03,433 --> 00:00:04,767
<i> But this is what happened.</i>

3
00:00:04,767 --> 00:00:06,767
<i> What? Can't show any concern?</i>

4
00:00:06,767 --> 00:00:09,100
<i>When my mother died,
we lost touch.</i>

5
00:00:09,100 --> 00:00:11,333
There's no more point for me to
<i> stay here now that he's gone!</i>

6
00:00:11,333 --> 00:00:13,767
<i> Son, it's okay to cry, okay?</i>

7
00:00:13,767 --> 00:00:16,267
<i> Uncle Frederico killed Papa?</i>

8
00:00:16,467 --> 00:00:18,333
<i> No! That's not true!</i>

9
00:00:18,333 --> 00:00:20,633
<i>- My daddy is not a murderer!
- [GUNSHOTS]</i>

10
00:00:20,633 --> 00:00:23,267
<i>Mr. Michael Fernandez and
Mr. Frederico Almazan</i>

11
00:00:23,267 --> 00:00:25,167
<i> killed each other.</i>

12
00:00:25,167 --> 00:00:26,400
<i> This case is closed.</i>

13
00:00:27,100 --> 00:00:29,167
<i> Papa, we're here now.</i>

14
00:00:29,167 --> 00:00:30,467
<i> And we're complete.</i>

15
00:00:34,800 --> 00:00:37,467
Mr. Fernandez has long
since settled his will.

16
00:00:37,467 --> 00:00:41,767
He left all his possessions
to his three children.

17
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:44,533
To you, Gio Cabrera,

18
00:00:44,533 --> 00:00:46,367
Martin Madrigal,

19
00:00:46,367 --> 00:00:48,167
and Francis Endaya.

20
00:00:49,367 --> 00:00:53,633
All of his properties will be
divided equally among us three,

21
00:00:53,633 --> 00:00:55,167
Including this hotel?

22
00:00:55,700 --> 00:00:59,400
Michael only owns
50 percent of Hotel 88.

23
00:01:00,700 --> 00:01:02,733
What? Someone else
owns shares of this hotel?

24
00:01:04,467 --> 00:01:06,000
[ATTORNEY]
A recent agreement was made...

25
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:09,200
...that 50 percent is owned
by Michael,

26
00:01:09,233 --> 00:01:10,800
while the other 50 percent

27
00:01:10,800 --> 00:01:13,000
goes directly to the
Almazan family.

28
00:01:13,533 --> 00:01:16,167
What?! That family?!

29
00:01:16,167 --> 00:01:18,167
According to investigations,
Attorney,

30
00:01:18,167 --> 00:01:20,500
Uncle Frederico killed
our father.

31
00:01:20,500 --> 00:01:22,733
Investigations show
that they killed each other.

32
00:01:22,733 --> 00:01:24,400
That's the same thing, Kiko!

33
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:26,333
Uncle Fred killed Papa!

34
00:01:26,333 --> 00:01:30,167
And they have a share
in this hotel that Papa built?

35
00:01:30,167 --> 00:01:31,467
That's unfair to us!

36
00:01:33,500 --> 00:01:36,733
The merger happened
before the tragedy.

37
00:01:36,733 --> 00:01:38,167
To be specific,

38
00:01:38,533 --> 00:01:41,033
the other 50 percent
mentioned in the agreement

39
00:01:41,067 --> 00:01:44,767
will go only to Frederico
Almazan's children.

40
00:01:44,767 --> 00:01:51,667
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

41
00:01:56,733 --> 00:02:03,667
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

42
00:02:54,733 --> 00:02:57,267
You heard our lawyer.

43
00:02:57,267 --> 00:03:00,167
You all have a share
in Hotel 88.

44
00:03:00,167 --> 00:03:03,600
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

45
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:06,133
Is that the reason
Uncle Michael and Dad made up?

46
00:03:10,767 --> 00:03:12,900
So we can be part-owners
of the hotel?

47
00:03:14,267 --> 00:03:16,400
Your dad didn't mention
anything about that.

48
00:03:17,767 --> 00:03:21,467
Maybe that's the reason
Uncle Michael killed Dad.

49
00:03:21,967 --> 00:03:25,533
Jade, the cops said
they killed each other.

50
00:03:25,533 --> 00:03:29,667
Leon, investigations show
Uncle Michael fired first.

51
00:03:29,667 --> 00:03:31,667
It means he was the one
with the intent to kill.

52
00:03:32,467 --> 00:03:33,633
My point is,

53
00:03:33,633 --> 00:03:35,867
we don't know how they
ended up in that situation.

54
00:03:35,867 --> 00:03:38,633
And my point is,
whatever their reason is,

55
00:03:38,633 --> 00:03:39,800
Dad is gone.

56
00:03:41,833 --> 00:03:43,267
The issue now is...

57
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:45,567
our stakes at the hotel.

58
00:03:46,333 --> 00:03:47,467
Okay?

59
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:50,400
What are we going to do
about our shares?

60
00:03:52,633 --> 00:03:54,933
Can't we just leave
the hotel to them?

61
00:03:59,633 --> 00:04:01,333
Dad had other businesses
he left behind.

62
00:04:02,200 --> 00:04:03,800
I need your help with them.

63
00:04:04,967 --> 00:04:06,300
I agree.

64
00:04:06,300 --> 00:04:09,500
You know what? I don't want
to be a part of anything

65
00:04:09,500 --> 00:04:11,167
related to Uncle Michael.

66
00:04:11,700 --> 00:04:13,367
But Dad wanted this for us.

67
00:04:13,367 --> 00:04:15,267
That's why he gave us
50 percent shares.

68
00:04:16,333 --> 00:04:17,867
I just want a
peaceful life, Luna.

69
00:04:17,867 --> 00:04:20,300
And I want justice for Dad!

70
00:04:20,700 --> 00:04:22,500
Luna, Leon...

71
00:04:23,467 --> 00:04:26,433
Now is not the time to argue.

72
00:04:28,767 --> 00:04:32,567
All I'm saying is this is
what Dad wanted for us.

73
00:04:35,700 --> 00:04:37,867
Can't we do this for him?

74
00:04:37,867 --> 00:04:43,800
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

75
00:04:45,700 --> 00:04:47,000
[KIKO]
You want to sell it?

76
00:04:47,767 --> 00:04:48,800
Yes.

77
00:04:50,233 --> 00:04:51,900
You can't.
This is Papa's legacy.

78
00:04:52,933 --> 00:04:55,867
I have the right to do
what I want with my shares.

79
00:04:55,867 --> 00:04:57,700
[GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]

80
00:04:57,700 --> 00:04:59,767
Papa left the hotel
with all three of us.

81
00:04:59,767 --> 00:05:01,667
We must decide together.

82
00:05:03,067 --> 00:05:04,567
What do you think, Martin?

83
00:05:06,067 --> 00:05:07,767
How about I sell you my shares?
Do you have the funds?

84
00:05:07,767 --> 00:05:12,400
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

85
00:05:12,400 --> 00:05:13,567
Well, Martin?

86
00:05:16,700 --> 00:05:18,933
I still have to look at the
pros and cons.

87
00:05:19,733 --> 00:05:20,800
At the end of the day,

88
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:23,233
this is still a promising
business opportunity.

89
00:05:23,867 --> 00:05:25,800
If you can't afford it,
I'll sell it to someone else.

90
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:28,033
Can you not be in such
a hurry to sell the hotel?

91
00:05:28,900 --> 00:05:29,900
Papa just died

92
00:05:29,900 --> 00:05:32,767
and you already want to
dispose of his legacy?

93
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:36,867
He wanted us to keep
the hotel running, remember?

94
00:05:37,767 --> 00:05:39,733
All of us three, together.

95
00:05:40,767 --> 00:05:42,933
He wanted us to start again.

96
00:05:44,300 --> 00:05:45,867
Shouldn't we at least try?

97
00:05:46,667 --> 00:05:49,467
All I'm saying is,
I need money.

98
00:05:50,333 --> 00:05:52,567
Money, not a pain
in the neck, Kiko.

99
00:05:53,933 --> 00:05:55,400
[SCOFFS]

100
00:06:00,667 --> 00:06:07,433
[MUSIC BOX PLAYING "FUR ELISE"
BY LUDWIG VAN BEETHOVEN]

101
00:06:07,467 --> 00:06:09,633
[FREDERICO]
<i> The mistakes we make...</i>

102
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:12,933
<i>...are what makes us
stronger in life.</i>

103
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:16,433
<i> So no matter what happened,</i>

104
00:06:17,633 --> 00:06:21,333
<i>I want you to remember
that I accept you, dear.</i>

105
00:06:21,333 --> 00:06:22,767
<i> I accept you.</i>

106
00:06:28,833 --> 00:06:29,933
[VOICE SHAKING]
<i> Dad...</i>

107
00:06:30,833 --> 00:06:31,933
<i> Dad.</i> [SNIFFLES]

108
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:34,467
<i> Dad, I'm sorry.</i>

109
00:06:34,467 --> 00:06:36,000
[WHIMPERS]

110
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:37,800
<i> Dad...</i> [SNIFFLES]

111
00:06:37,800 --> 00:06:39,733
[BREATH QUIVERS]

112
00:06:41,667 --> 00:06:44,733
[SOBBING] I'm sorry, Dad!

113
00:06:44,733 --> 00:06:46,000
<i> Dear...</i>

114
00:06:46,967 --> 00:06:48,800
<i> Dear, it's okay.</i>

115
00:06:50,133 --> 00:06:52,867
<i> I'm scared. I'm scared, Dad.</i>

116
00:06:52,867 --> 00:06:55,500
<i> Daddy's here. Okay?</i>

117
00:06:55,500 --> 00:06:56,900
[CRIES]

118
00:06:56,900 --> 00:06:59,100
<i>You don't have to worry
about anything anymore.</i>

119
00:07:00,133 --> 00:07:01,633
<i> I'll take care of it.</i>

120
00:07:02,167 --> 00:07:05,667
<i>Just leave everything
you've done here, okay?</i>

121
00:07:06,500 --> 00:07:07,800
And you're coming home with me.

122
00:07:09,467 --> 00:07:12,333
<i>I'll fix everything
for you, okay?</i>

123
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:14,633
- [SOBS]
<i> - Stop crying.</i>

124
00:07:15,100 --> 00:07:16,433
[CRANKS]

125
00:07:16,433 --> 00:07:21,067
<i>- I kept this in the car.
- [MUSIC BOX PLAYING]</i>

126
00:07:21,067 --> 00:07:24,167
<i>I've been hoping
you'd come home to us.</i>

127
00:07:24,167 --> 00:07:30,767
[MUSIC BOX CONTINUES PLAYING]

128
00:07:30,767 --> 00:07:32,067
[LUNA] I promise, Dad.

129
00:07:32,067 --> 00:07:34,400
<i> I will do everything for you.</i>

130
00:07:35,533 --> 00:07:37,033
<i> For our family.</i>

131
00:07:38,033 --> 00:07:39,833
<i> No matter what it takes.</i>

132
00:07:52,733 --> 00:07:54,167
What's the emergency?

133
00:07:55,567 --> 00:07:57,400
We have guests.

134
00:08:00,533 --> 00:08:05,733
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

135
00:08:07,567 --> 00:08:08,867
Or should I say...

136
00:08:11,867 --> 00:08:13,167
...co-owners.

137
00:08:15,633 --> 00:08:22,533
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

138
00:08:51,067 --> 00:08:57,933
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

139
00:09:03,533 --> 00:09:04,900
What are you doing here?

140
00:09:05,800 --> 00:09:07,500
We have a right to this place.

141
00:09:07,500 --> 00:09:08,467
We know.

142
00:09:08,467 --> 00:09:10,933
But you shouldn't have
come unannounced.

143
00:09:11,833 --> 00:09:13,700
I'll go straight to the point.

144
00:09:13,700 --> 00:09:15,733
We want to buy your shares.

145
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:19,967
Who told you we're selling?

146
00:09:19,967 --> 00:09:26,900
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

147
00:09:41,467 --> 00:09:42,767
Buy us out?

148
00:09:43,667 --> 00:09:44,667
Are you joking?

149
00:09:46,333 --> 00:09:48,133
Do I look like I'm joking?

150
00:09:48,133 --> 00:09:50,000
I think it's better
if you just leave

151
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:52,300
because we're not selling
this place.

152
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:55,000
Are you seriously
kicking us out?

153
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:57,800
Technically, this place
belongs to us too, doesn't it?

154
00:09:58,900 --> 00:10:00,333
It's not like that, I just--

155
00:10:00,333 --> 00:10:02,767
That's exactly what
you wanted to say, right, Kiko?

156
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,200
Which is funny.

157
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:09,100
- Coming from you?
- [MARTIN] Coming from you?

158
00:10:09,100 --> 00:10:11,333
What does that even mean?

159
00:10:11,333 --> 00:10:13,967
You're talking like
you're somebody.

160
00:10:15,067 --> 00:10:16,167
What?

161
00:10:16,167 --> 00:10:18,000
I know you, Luna.

162
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:20,267
I know everything you've done.

163
00:10:20,267 --> 00:10:22,200
- Martin, please.
- What?

164
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:24,400
Can't you hear
what your sister's saying?

165
00:10:24,400 --> 00:10:26,700
I'm sure she means
nothing by it.

166
00:10:26,700 --> 00:10:28,400
- Yeah, sure, sure.
- Right, Luna?

167
00:10:28,400 --> 00:10:30,067
Leon, please.

168
00:10:30,067 --> 00:10:32,067
- Don't take their side!
- [GIO] Fine, fine!

169
00:10:32,700 --> 00:10:34,133
Take my share.

170
00:10:35,367 --> 00:10:36,833
Let's just finish this!

171
00:10:41,100 --> 00:10:42,200
How much?

172
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:46,767
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

173
00:10:47,400 --> 00:10:48,700
Two million.

174
00:10:49,233 --> 00:10:51,267
You can take it now, cash.

175
00:10:53,867 --> 00:10:55,267
Same goes for everyone.

176
00:10:55,267 --> 00:11:02,200
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

177
00:11:02,933 --> 00:11:04,033
No.

178
00:11:05,367 --> 00:11:07,233
Shove that money in your chest!

179
00:11:07,233 --> 00:11:08,767
Hey, don't talk
to her like that!

180
00:11:08,800 --> 00:11:10,100
Hey!
That's enough! Enough!

181
00:11:10,100 --> 00:11:12,067
Can we stop? Enough!

182
00:11:12,067 --> 00:11:13,233
Come on!

183
00:11:13,233 --> 00:11:14,900
We're not kids anymore.

184
00:11:14,900 --> 00:11:17,467
[HUFFS] Your sister's
the one losing it.

185
00:11:17,467 --> 00:11:19,567
Let's talk this out calmly.

186
00:11:19,567 --> 00:11:21,833
You're the ones
who just barged in!

187
00:11:21,833 --> 00:11:23,567
- Just leave already!
- [LUNA] No, no!

188
00:11:23,567 --> 00:11:25,900
We have a stake here too,
right?

189
00:11:25,900 --> 00:11:27,567
This conversation's
going nowhere!

190
00:11:27,567 --> 00:11:29,067
This one's going
to go somewhere!

191
00:11:29,067 --> 00:11:31,100
- Go on, try me!
- Let go of me!

192
00:11:31,100 --> 00:11:32,900
Enough! Enough!

193
00:11:32,900 --> 00:11:35,233
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

194
00:11:35,233 --> 00:11:37,333
- Jade, Luna, let's go!
- No, Leon, no!

195
00:11:37,333 --> 00:11:39,900
- We do have a stake here!
- I said let's go!

196
00:11:39,900 --> 00:11:41,233
Let's go!

197
00:11:41,267 --> 00:11:47,267
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

198
00:11:47,267 --> 00:11:48,400
[LEON] Come on!

199
00:11:50,033 --> 00:11:51,100
Justin!

200
00:11:52,433 --> 00:11:54,133
- Let's go, Justin.
- Let's go.

201
00:11:55,467 --> 00:12:02,100
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

202
00:12:16,467 --> 00:12:23,433
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

203
00:12:25,467 --> 00:12:28,200
You shouldn't have said
you'd sell the shares.

204
00:12:28,867 --> 00:12:30,500
I need the money, okay!

205
00:12:31,333 --> 00:12:34,467
Hey, hey, hey, eat first.

206
00:12:34,467 --> 00:12:37,633
Bro, didn't you think about
whether they can be trusted?

207
00:12:37,633 --> 00:12:39,900
Why did our fathers
even end up like that?

208
00:12:39,900 --> 00:12:41,867
It means he was furious
at Uncle Fed,

209
00:12:41,867 --> 00:12:43,467
and you still want
to sell to them?

210
00:12:43,467 --> 00:12:45,367
[MONETTE] Wait, remember, okay?

211
00:12:45,367 --> 00:12:48,033
There are only three of you,
there are four of them.

212
00:12:48,067 --> 00:12:51,333
- So?
- You're clearly outnumbered.

213
00:12:51,333 --> 00:12:54,633
So you should stick together,
not fight.

214
00:13:00,500 --> 00:13:07,467
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

215
00:13:15,267 --> 00:13:16,867
Ma?

216
00:13:16,867 --> 00:13:18,233
Ma, Ma, Ma!

217
00:13:18,233 --> 00:13:20,167
Ma! Ma, no--

218
00:13:20,167 --> 00:13:21,267
Ma!

219
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:22,933
- Oh my God, Ma!
- [GROANS]

220
00:13:22,933 --> 00:13:24,000
Ma...

221
00:13:24,933 --> 00:13:26,200
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

222
00:13:26,200 --> 00:13:28,033
You scared me, Ma.

223
00:13:28,033 --> 00:13:30,033
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

224
00:13:30,033 --> 00:13:32,167
I fell asleep.

225
00:13:32,900 --> 00:13:34,233
I was waiting for you.

226
00:13:34,233 --> 00:13:36,267
[PILLS RATTLING]

227
00:13:36,467 --> 00:13:40,167
Tell me, what happened?

228
00:13:44,033 --> 00:13:45,433
[SIGHS]

229
00:13:45,433 --> 00:13:47,067
They don't want to sell, Ma.

230
00:13:49,633 --> 00:13:52,433
But I'll do everything
to get it from them.

231
00:13:55,300 --> 00:13:59,533
Are you sure
that's what your Dad wanted?

232
00:14:05,300 --> 00:14:07,533
[SIGHS]

233
00:14:10,633 --> 00:14:12,933
I don't know, Ma.

234
00:14:16,067 --> 00:14:18,433
All I know is Dad
needs justice.

235
00:14:20,333 --> 00:14:23,067
And this is the only way
I can give it to him.

236
00:14:24,733 --> 00:14:27,367
This is what you want too
for him, right, Ma?

237
00:14:29,033 --> 00:14:30,300
[SOBBING SOFTLY]

238
00:14:30,300 --> 00:14:31,500
Of course.

239
00:14:32,267 --> 00:14:33,633
Of course, dear.

240
00:14:37,367 --> 00:14:38,567
Yes.

241
00:14:39,433 --> 00:14:46,400
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

242
00:14:52,267 --> 00:14:55,000
Draw something
that makes you happy.

243
00:14:55,667 --> 00:14:57,500
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

244
00:15:04,033 --> 00:15:05,133
Ugh.

245
00:15:06,500 --> 00:15:07,833
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

246
00:15:08,500 --> 00:15:10,500
Dad...

247
00:15:10,500 --> 00:15:12,700
This is so hard, Dad.

248
00:15:12,700 --> 00:15:13,967
I miss you.

249
00:15:15,033 --> 00:15:17,700
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

250
00:15:19,567 --> 00:15:21,100
But I'll try.

251
00:15:23,467 --> 00:15:27,667
I'll try because I know
this is what you'd want for me.

252
00:15:28,867 --> 00:15:31,867
- [EDWARD PANTING]
- [SIGHS] Okay, Jade.

253
00:15:31,867 --> 00:15:32,867
Okay, Jade.

254
00:15:32,867 --> 00:15:34,767
Let's find something
that makes you happy.

255
00:15:35,500 --> 00:15:42,467
["PANGHABANG IKAW"
BY DARREN PLAYING]

256
00:15:57,100 --> 00:16:04,033
["PANGHABANG IKAW"
CONTINUES PLAYING]

257
00:16:17,900 --> 00:16:24,867
["PANGHABANG IKAW"
CONTINUES PLAYING]

258
00:16:38,767 --> 00:16:45,733
["PANGHABANG IKAW"
CONTINUES PLAYING]

259
00:16:46,900 --> 00:16:48,133
- Hey!
- Oh!

260
00:16:52,100 --> 00:16:53,600
What is that?

261
00:16:54,067 --> 00:16:55,533
You're giving it to me?

262
00:17:00,133 --> 00:17:01,867
- Jade!
- [JADE CHUCKLING]

263
00:17:10,633 --> 00:17:12,867
I'm sorry for what I said
to Luna.

264
00:17:15,300 --> 00:17:16,933
I just got carried away.

265
00:17:19,800 --> 00:17:20,967
I know.

266
00:17:24,033 --> 00:17:26,000
What are you planning
to do with the hotel?

267
00:17:26,767 --> 00:17:28,000
Honestly...

268
00:17:28,833 --> 00:17:30,133
...I don't know yet.

269
00:17:30,133 --> 00:17:37,100
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

270
00:17:38,167 --> 00:17:40,633
Our dads killed each other!

271
00:17:42,133 --> 00:17:44,667
Did you ever think
that would happen?

272
00:17:45,267 --> 00:17:46,733
No.

273
00:17:48,733 --> 00:17:49,933
Not ever.

274
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:52,867
[SNIFFLING]

275
00:17:52,867 --> 00:17:56,867
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

276
00:17:57,800 --> 00:17:59,000
Can we...

277
00:17:59,867 --> 00:18:01,767
...not fight over the hotel?

278
00:18:02,633 --> 00:18:04,933
I'll talk to my siblings.

279
00:18:10,233 --> 00:18:12,167
I'll talk to my brothers too.

280
00:18:14,200 --> 00:18:20,300
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

281
00:18:22,233 --> 00:18:24,233
It would be a shame if you'd
just abandon the hotel.

282
00:18:24,233 --> 00:18:25,867
We can still
continue operating.

283
00:18:25,867 --> 00:18:27,167
You're good at this.

284
00:18:27,167 --> 00:18:28,367
You can get it
back on its feet.

285
00:18:29,400 --> 00:18:31,267
[SIGHS] What choice do we have?

286
00:18:31,267 --> 00:18:38,200
- [FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]
- [FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

287
00:18:39,833 --> 00:18:41,167
[KIKO] Let's go downstairs.

288
00:18:57,200 --> 00:18:59,767
So, we won't be selling it
anymore, right?

289
00:18:59,767 --> 00:19:02,200
That means we can
open the hotel for business.

290
00:19:03,267 --> 00:19:04,800
Whether we'll be selling it
or not,

291
00:19:04,800 --> 00:19:06,700
we need to know its status.

292
00:19:07,600 --> 00:19:10,800
What needs replacing

293
00:19:10,800 --> 00:19:12,433
or repairing.

294
00:19:19,633 --> 00:19:23,867
[OBJECTS THUD]

295
00:19:27,767 --> 00:19:29,433
[CLICKING]

296
00:19:35,400 --> 00:19:37,633
Looks like
a lot needs replacing.

297
00:19:37,633 --> 00:19:44,600
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

298
00:19:45,667 --> 00:19:47,233
[DOOR OPENS, CREAKS]

299
00:19:48,800 --> 00:19:51,133
Papa's room
still looks the same.

300
00:19:52,267 --> 00:19:53,433
[DOOR CLOSES]

301
00:19:55,967 --> 00:19:57,800
But there are
a lot more things here now.

302
00:19:57,800 --> 00:20:00,867
- [PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [OBJECT CLINKS]

303
00:20:15,700 --> 00:20:21,967
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

304
00:20:22,833 --> 00:20:24,300
Oh, Martin.

305
00:20:24,967 --> 00:20:26,600
Do you remember this drawer?

306
00:20:28,267 --> 00:20:30,233
There would always be
chips here for us.

307
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:32,933
[MARTIN]
That drawer looks worn out.

308
00:20:32,933 --> 00:20:34,567
We may need to replace it, too.

309
00:20:37,300 --> 00:20:38,633
This used to be my favorite.

310
00:20:45,367 --> 00:20:48,367
Papa used to be fond
of recording, right?

311
00:20:48,367 --> 00:20:53,633
[OBJECT RUSTLES]

312
00:20:56,400 --> 00:20:57,833
Chips and a videocam?

313
00:20:58,667 --> 00:21:00,367
What a way to chill.

314
00:21:00,367 --> 00:21:02,033
Oh, maybe we still have
a video here

315
00:21:02,033 --> 00:21:03,633
while we were swimming.

316
00:21:11,067 --> 00:21:12,333
[CAMERA CLICKS, CHIMES]

317
00:21:12,333 --> 00:21:13,900
[STATIC NOISE]

318
00:21:20,900 --> 00:21:22,333
[MICHAEL BREATHES DEEPLY]

319
00:21:23,433 --> 00:21:24,533
<i> Kids.</i>

320
00:21:24,533 --> 00:21:30,467
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

321
00:21:32,433 --> 00:21:33,900
[GIO] Do you really want
to watch that?

322
00:21:35,567 --> 00:21:37,067
Don't play it.

323
00:21:37,067 --> 00:21:38,367
If you don't want it,
that's fine.

324
00:21:38,367 --> 00:21:40,000
I'll just tell you
all about it later.

325
00:21:44,133 --> 00:21:45,200
[MICHAEL] Kids.

326
00:21:46,233 --> 00:21:47,900
<i>If you're watching this
right now,</i>

327
00:21:47,900 --> 00:21:50,767
<i>I probably didn't have
the chance</i>

328
00:21:50,767 --> 00:21:52,733
<i> to say it to you in person.</i>

329
00:21:55,700 --> 00:21:58,233
<i>I had my fair share
of shortcomings as a dad.</i>

330
00:21:59,200 --> 00:22:00,900
<i> Moments when I fell short.</i>

331
00:22:00,900 --> 00:22:01,933
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

332
00:22:01,933 --> 00:22:03,700
<i>I've failed you
in so many ways.</i>

333
00:22:04,800 --> 00:22:08,200
<i>Many of them I might not
be able to make it up to.</i>

334
00:22:08,200 --> 00:22:09,933
<i> When weakness....</i>

335
00:22:11,133 --> 00:22:12,700
<i> got the better of me.</i>

336
00:22:13,800 --> 00:22:15,900
<i> Moments where</i>

337
00:22:15,933 --> 00:22:18,267
I wish I had more courage so...

338
00:22:19,267 --> 00:22:22,900
<i>I could've fought harder
for what's yours.</i>

339
00:22:22,900 --> 00:22:23,900
<i> What's for us.</i>

340
00:22:25,167 --> 00:22:27,067
[MICHAEL SIGHS] Unfortunately,

341
00:22:28,267 --> 00:22:30,633
<i> your father is weak.</i>

342
00:22:30,633 --> 00:22:33,767
<i> I just let destiny</i>

343
00:22:33,767 --> 00:22:36,067
<i> decide for me.</i>

344
00:22:37,400 --> 00:22:39,133
<i> Kids,</i>

345
00:22:39,133 --> 00:22:42,067
<i>if you're ever unable
to forgive me,</i>

346
00:22:43,400 --> 00:22:44,900
<i> I'll understand.</i>

347
00:22:46,133 --> 00:22:48,167
<i> I guess I don't deserve it.</i>

348
00:22:48,200 --> 00:22:50,467
<i> But Gio,</i>

349
00:22:50,467 --> 00:22:52,100
<i> Martin, Kiko...</i>

350
00:22:55,033 --> 00:22:57,267
[TONGUE CLICKS]
<i> I love you all so much.</i>

351
00:22:58,667 --> 00:22:59,967
<i> In fact,</i>

352
00:22:59,967 --> 00:23:02,767
<i> everything I did,</i>

353
00:23:02,767 --> 00:23:04,300
<i> every decision I made,</i>

354
00:23:05,367 --> 00:23:07,800
<i> even the wrong decisions,</i>

355
00:23:07,800 --> 00:23:11,267
I did all of it to protect you.

356
00:23:12,700 --> 00:23:15,233
<i>I want your future
to be secured.</i>

357
00:23:17,267 --> 00:23:18,400
[TONGUE CLICKS] Here.

358
00:23:19,300 --> 00:23:21,133
<i> Here at this hotel.</i>

359
00:23:21,133 --> 00:23:23,067
<i> Hotel 88.</i>

360
00:23:26,167 --> 00:23:29,200
<i>This place is filled
with beautiful memories.</i>

361
00:23:29,200 --> 00:23:32,500
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

362
00:23:32,500 --> 00:23:34,967
<i>That's why
I'm sincerely asking you,</i>

363
00:23:34,967 --> 00:23:37,233
<i> please don't sell Hotel 88.</i>

364
00:23:37,233 --> 00:23:42,400
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

365
00:23:42,400 --> 00:23:44,267
<i> Because this is your home.</i>

366
00:23:48,167 --> 00:23:50,200
<i> And I want you to know,</i>

367
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:52,133
- [STATIC NOISE]
<i> - that there's a hidden--</i>

368
00:23:52,133 --> 00:23:54,700
Oh... what happened?

369
00:23:55,833 --> 00:23:57,167
The file is likely
to be corrupted.

370
00:23:57,167 --> 00:23:59,533
Forget it.
He's saying nonsense.

371
00:23:59,533 --> 00:24:01,367
[KIKO] Didn't you hear him?

372
00:24:01,367 --> 00:24:04,533
He said there's something
we need to know.

373
00:24:04,533 --> 00:24:06,933
And I think
that if we lose this hotel,

374
00:24:06,933 --> 00:24:08,867
we'll never be able to find out
what that is.

375
00:24:10,433 --> 00:24:12,500
I just need money, ASAP.

376
00:24:13,833 --> 00:24:16,833
[MARTIN] It's not easy to sell
a property of this size.

377
00:24:17,733 --> 00:24:19,200
Okay?

378
00:24:19,200 --> 00:24:20,333
It will take time.

379
00:24:21,333 --> 00:24:23,233
You know that.
You're in real estate.

380
00:24:25,200 --> 00:24:28,233
So I don't think that's
the solution to your problem.

381
00:24:31,067 --> 00:24:32,900
What are you trying to say?

382
00:24:32,900 --> 00:24:34,767
What I'm trying to say is that

383
00:24:34,767 --> 00:24:36,867
if we make this hotel
operational,

384
00:24:37,933 --> 00:24:39,533
you'll be able to earn extra.

385
00:24:41,267 --> 00:24:43,067
The three of us will be able
to profit from it.

386
00:24:43,967 --> 00:24:50,933
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

387
00:25:00,200 --> 00:25:04,033
[MUSIC TURNS FOREBODING]

388
00:25:04,067 --> 00:25:06,567
[PHONE RINGING]

389
00:25:06,567 --> 00:25:07,533
Hello?

390
00:25:08,967 --> 00:25:10,100
I'm here.

391
00:25:10,100 --> 00:25:17,033
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

392
00:25:21,500 --> 00:25:23,300
<i>The re-opening of the hotel
will push through.</i>

393
00:25:23,300 --> 00:25:25,433
<i> We have to treat them kindly.</i>

394
00:25:25,433 --> 00:25:26,933
<i> Was that meant for me?</i>

395
00:25:26,933 --> 00:25:28,100
<i> There's no 50 million pesos</i>

396
00:25:28,100 --> 00:25:31,300
<i>and the hotel owes money
to the bank.</i>

397
00:25:31,300 --> 00:25:33,267
<i> If it doesn't get settled...</i>

398
00:25:33,267 --> 00:25:34,833
<i> We'll lose the hotel.</i>

399
00:25:34,833 --> 00:25:36,833
<i>They left a hotel
and tons of problems.</i>

400
00:25:36,867 --> 00:25:40,033
<i>We only have one guest,
and now you think ill of him.</i>

401
00:25:40,033 --> 00:25:41,200
<i> Do you need anything?</i>

402
00:25:41,200 --> 00:25:42,600
<i>Who knows
what he could be up to?</i>

403
00:25:42,600 --> 00:25:44,300
<i> What if he's a thief?</i>

404
00:25:44,300 --> 00:25:46,233
[WIND CHIMES CLINKING]

